<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Macphail half year loss plunges.</title>
<headline>Macphail half year loss plunges.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-02-26</dateline>
<text>
<p>Half year ended Dec 31</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr, attrib (cts)     97.9 loss   vs 12.5 loss</p>
<p>    Div (cts)		 nil	   vs 13.5</p>
<p>    Attrib loss	     23.39	 vs 2.98</p>
<p>    Pre-tax loss	    23.30	 vs 2.58</p>
<p>    Tax			 0.04	  vs 0.58</p>
<p>    Interest received     1.97 paid   vs 0.21</p>
<p>    Turnover		  211.94	vs 255.98</p>
<p>Full name:</p>
<p>Loss on UK operations/exports 17.63 vs 0.65</p>
<p>NOTE - Macphail said the loss for the period was largely attributrable to the writedowns in -- and subsequent disposal of -- its UK operations.</p>
<p>The firm said that it expected to return to at least a break even position over the next six months.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
